===Etymology===
Arabic ''muslimun'' is the stem IV [[w:Arabic_grammar#Participle|participle]]<ref>also known as "infinitive", c.f. Burns & Ralph, ''World Civilizations'', 5th ed., p. 371</ref> of the [[triliteral]] ''[[w:S-L-M|S-L-M]]'' "to be whole, intact". A literal translation would be "one who wants or seeks wholeness", where "wholeness" translates ''islāmun''. In a religious sense, ''[[w:Islam|Al-Islām]]'' translates to "faith, piety", and ''Muslim'' to "one who has (religious) faith or piety".

